NEW YORK, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar appreciated noticeably in late trading on Tuesday as market participants sought safe havens amid the ongoing Russia-Ukraine conflict. The dollar index, which measures the greenback against six major peers, rose 0.73 percent at 97.4090. In late New York trading, the euro fell to 1.1131 U.S. dollars from 1.1226 dollars in the previous session, and the British pound was down to 1.3314 dollars from 1.3419 U.S. dollars in the previous session. The Australian dollar decreased to 0.7251 U.S. dollar from 0.7264 dollar. The U.S. dollar bought 114.87 Japanese yen, lower than 114.88 Japanese yen of the previous session. The U.S. dollar rose to 0.9189 Swiss franc from 0.9167 Swiss franc, and it was up to 1.2739 Canadian dollars from 1.2690 Canadian dollars.  â– 